description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to work within Dorset Leg Ulcer Service as a Leg Ulcer Staff Nurse. This post is either a fixed term or secondment post for 9 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Leg Ulcer Service requires a Band 5 Leg Ulcer Staff Nurse to work 15 hours per week within the Leg Ulcer Service in West Dorset. The post holder will be responsible for running the leg ulcer clinics from 8.30am - 5pm. The post holder will be supported by a dedicated Health Care Support worker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support and training will be given by Leg Ulcer Nurse Specialists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There would also be ample opportunities to work extra hours on a bank contract to cover annual leave and sickness within team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments. This will only apply to candidates who are new to the Trust and not internal staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sara Pato, Leg Ulcer Nurse Specialist/Manager, Email address: sara.pato@nhs.net, Telephone number: 01202 443739&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquires very welcomed for more details&lt;/p&gt;
